## Tool #1: CSRF PoC Generator (Burp Suite)
### Best for: Generating proof-of-concept HTML attacks
### Installation
Burp Suite already includes this. No separate installation needed.
**Download Burp Suite:**
```bash
# Linux
wget https://portswigger.net/burp/releases/download?product=community&version=2023.12.1&type=Linux
# Run
java -jar burp_community_linux_v2023_12_1.sh


Tool #2: XSRFProbe
Best for: Comprehensive CSRF scanning
Installation
bash
# Method 1: pip (Recommended)
pip3 install xsrfprobe
# Method 2: From source
git clone https://github.com/0xInfection/XSRFProbe.git
cd XSRFProbe
python3 setup.py install
# Method 3: Docker
docker pull 0xinfection/xsrfprobe

Basic Usage
bash
# Scan single URL
xsrfprobe -u https://target.com/transfer -m POST -d "amount=1000&to=attacker"
# Scan with cookie
xsrfprobe -u https://target.com/settings -c "sessionid=abc123"
# Scan entire site (crawl mode)
xsrfprobe -u https://target.com --crawl
# Output to file
xsrfprobe -u https://target.com/api -o csrf_report.json
# Verbose mode for debugging
xsrfprobe -u https://target.com --verbose

Advanced Configuration
bash
# Scan with custom headers
xsrfprobe -u https://target.com/change-email \
  -H "X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"attacker@evil.com"}'
# Use proxy (Burp Suite)
xsrfprobe -u https://target.com --proxy http://127.0.0.1:8080
# Thread count for speed
xsrfprobe -u https://target.com --threads 20
# Test specific CSRF vectors only
xsrfprobe -u https://target.com --test-methods token-removal,token-manipulation


Tool #3: CRLFuzz
Best for: Header injection + CSRF chain attacks
Installation
bash
# Go installation required first
# Install Go: https://golang.org/dl/
# Install CRLFuzz
go install -v github.com/dwisiswant0/crlfuzz/cmd/crlfuzz@latest
# Verify installation
crlfuzz --version
Basic Usage
bash
# Single URL scan
crlfuzz -u "https://target.com/transfer?amount=1000"
# Read from file
crlfuzz -l urls.txt
# Output results
crlfuzz -u "https://target.com" -o results.txt
# Use custom headers
crlfuzz -u "https://target.com" -H "User-Agent: CRLFuzz" -H "X-Custom: test"
# Threading for speed
crlfuzz -l urls.txt -t 50
CSRF-Specific Usage
bash

# Test for Host header injection (can lead to CSRF)
crlfuzz -u "https://target.com" -p "Host: attacker.com%0d%0aX-Custom:"
# Test for Referer bypass
crlfuzz -u "https://target.com" -H "Referer: https://attacker.com"
# Test with CRLF injection for CSRF token leak
crlfuzz -u "https://target.com/api/transfer" -d "amount=1000%0d%0aCSRF-Token:"
